FBIS4-19067 "drweu071_l_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-071 Daily Report 12 Apr 1994 SPAIN Yeltsin: Use of Force Could Lead to `Interminable' War Yeltsin: Use of Force Could Lead to `Interminable' War LD1204140794 Madrid TVE Internacional Television in Spanish 1300 GMT 12 Apr 94 LD1204140794 Madrid TVE Internacional Television Spanish BFN [Excerpts] Boris Yeltsin, speaking in Madrid, has again commented on the crisis in Bosnia. He has done so to repeat that the Western policy of punishing the Serbs is dangerous and can aggravate the war. Despite Russia's fear, NATO could step up military pressure on the Bosnian Serbs. [passage omitted] [Begin Yeltsin recording in Russian with superimposed translation into Spanish] The only thing that the use of force in Bosnia will achieve is to turn the war into something constant, interminable. Should the conflict escalate, responsibility will fall on those who have decided to use force in Bosnia. [end recording]
